  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Water, Social Mobilization/Hygiene promotion and Capacity Building Interventions for Acute Watery Diarrhoea-Affected Populations in 5 woredas of Southern Nations, Nationalities, and People&#x2019;s Region (SNNPR) and Oromiya</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As emergency response to AWD outbreak, ACF plans to distribute in 5 woredas    49,941 strips of Aqua-tab household water treatment chemical (for 3 months), water container (5,549 Jericans and 5549 buckets), and   22,196  soaps for four months to  5,549 households. In addition the response will reach 219,402 beneficiaries (One fifth of the populations of the total of 5 woredas) through AWD focused hygiene and sanitation promotion messages and campaigns. For proper hygiene promotion it will give AWD response focused training for 200 health workers. ACF will also make capacity building of woredas to support the non- medical items for CTC (like tankers with 10,000 liters capacity, knapsack sprayers, drum of HTH chlorine and tents).
ACF has made discussion with other organizations like IRC, GOAL, PIE and CARE to avoid overlap in the project locations. Accordingly, it will implement the above mentioned activities in terms of WASH in 5 woredas of Sidama zone ( Loka Abaya) Hararge zone (Tulo, Girawa, Mesela) and  Borena zone (Moyale).</narrative>
  </description>
